NAME

     $current_package/1  -- get the name of the current package
   

FORMS

     $current_package(Package)


DESCRIPTION

     Gets the name of the package loaded in the system. 
     If no package is loaded in the system, "Package" will be
     unified with the integer -1.





NAME
 
     $get_default_proc/3  -- get the default procedure whose default procedure
                             table index is given


FORMS

     $get_default_proc(Idx,Pred,Arity)


DESCRIPTION

     Gets name and arity of the default procedure whose default procedure
     table index is given. The first argument must be an integer and 
     a correct default procedure table index. If it is not, this predicate
     fails.






NAME

     $get_default_use/2  -- get the default use module whose default use
                            module table index is given.


FORMS

     $get_default_use(Idx,ModName)


DESCRIPTION

     Gets the name of a module in the default use module table.
     The first argument must be an integer and a correct default use
     module table index. If it is not, this predicate fails.






NAME

     $listasm_clause/2  -- list the clause in the assembler syntax


FORMS

     $listasm_clause(DBRef,PckgName)


DESCRIPTION

     Prints the given clause in the PharLap 386|ASM assembler syntax
     in the current output stream. The first argument is the data base
     reference of the clause, and the second argument is the name of the
     package being created. 


NOTES

     See packaging documentation for more information.






NAME

     $listasm_ntblentry/4  -- list the name table entry in the assembler syntax


FORMS

     $listasm_ntblentry(Module,Pred,Arity,PckgName)


DESCRIPTION

     Prints the name table entry of the given procedure in the PharLap 
     386|ASM assembler syntax in the current output stream. The first three
     arguments represent the procedure, and the last argument is the name
     of the package being created. 


NOTES

     See packaging documentation for more information.






NAME

     $ntblentry/3  -- print the address of the name table entry


FORMS

     $ntblentry(Module,Pred,Arity)


DESCRIPTION

     Prints the address of the name table entry of the given procedure 
     in the hexadecimal format. This predicate is used to produce 
     unique names for packaged procedures.


NOTES

     See packaging documentation for more information.





NAME

     $package_external_defs/0  -- Put "extrn" directives into the package file


FORMS

     $package_external_defs


DESCRIPTION

     Puts "extrn" directives into the package file. 


NOTES

     See packaging documentation for more information.






NAME

     $package_toktbl/1  -- Copy the system token table in the packaging   
                           token table.


FORMS

     $package_toktbl(NumofToks)


DESCRIPTION

     Copies the system token table into the package token file, and
     returns the number of tokens.


NOTES

     See packaging documentation for more information.



